article.headline: Williamson scores 23 as Bucknell knocks off American 80-57 in Patriot League Tournament

article.linkText: Williamson scores 23 as Bucknell knocks off American 80-57 in Patriot League Tournament
article.story: WASHINGTON -- — Noah Williamson had 23 points in fifth-seeded Bucknell's 80-57 win against fourth-seeded American on Thursday night in the Patriot League Tournament. Williamson also had 10 rebounds for the Bison (14-18), who play at top-seeded Colgate in the semifinals on Sunday. Jack Forrest scored 16 points and added seven rebounds. Elvin Edmonds IV had 13 points and shot 5 of 9 from the field and 3 of 4 from the free-throw line. Lorenzo Donadio led the way for the Eagles (16-15, 0-1) with 16 points and six rebounds. American also got 13 points and two blocks from Matt Rogers. Geoff Sprouse also had nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
